Explanation:

User: Initiates a request to access www.foobar.com through a web browser.
Domain Name: www.foobar.com is resolved to the server's IP address (8.8.8.8) by the DNS server.
DNS Server: Resolves the domain name to the server's IP address using DNS records.
Server: Hosts the website and consists of:
Nginx (Web Server): Handles HTTP requests, serves static content, and forwards dynamic requests to the application server.
Application Server: Executes application logic, generates dynamic content, and interacts with the database.
MySQL (Database): Stores and manages website data.
